  "title": "Trust Situated Knowing",
  "story": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "40e072fa5391e87f",
      "text": "Modern science, economics, law and other fields often purport that their forms of knowledge are more or less universal and invariant to which individual experience, subjective insights, and local knowledge must be subordinated as less reliable and useful."
    },
    {
      "type": "video",
      "id": "67c719ee9ccebfcf",
